Definition: an ancient country and wine producing region in the east of the Balkan Peninsula to the north of the Aegean Sea
Example: colonized by ancient Greeks; later a Roman province; now divided between Bulgaria and Greece and Turkey
Synonyms: geographical_area, i, Balkan_Peninsula, p, an, ancient, country, and, wine, producing, region, in, the, east, of, Balkan, Peninsula, to, north, Aegean, Sea, colonized, by, Greeks, later, a, Roman, province, now, divided, between, Bulgaria, Greece, Turkey
Category: noun.location
